question: What are the names of products that have been reviewed with a rating greater than 4, along with their average rating?
sql: SELECT p.product_name, AVG(r.review_rating) AS average_rating FROM products p JOIN reviews r ON p.product_id = r.review_product_id WHERE r.review_rating > 4 GROUP BY p.product_name;

question: Which users have placed an order with a total value greater than $50, and what are their email addresses?
sql: SELECT u.user_name, u.user_email FROM users u JOIN orders o ON u.user_id = o.order_user_id WHERE o.order_total > 50;

question: What are the product names and their corresponding categories for products that are supplied by more than one vendor?
sql: SELECT p.product_name, c.category_name FROM products p JOIN category_products cp ON p.product_id = cp.category_product_product_id JOIN categories c ON cp.category_product_category_id = c.category_id JOIN product_vendors pv ON p.product_id = pv.product_vendor_product_id GROUP BY p.product_name, c.category_name HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT pv.product_vendor_vendor_id) > 1;

question: List the order IDs and total values for orders that have been shipped, along with their shipment status?
sql: SELECT o.order_id, o.order_total, s.shipment_status FROM orders o JOIN shipments s ON o.order_id = s.shipment_order_id WHERE s.shipment_status = 'shipped';

question: What are the coupon codes and their discount percentages for coupons that are valid between '2022-01-01' and '2022-12-31'?
sql: SELECT c.coupon_code, c.coupon_discount_percentage FROM coupons c WHERE c.coupon_start_date <= '2022-12-31' AND c.coupon_end_date >= '2022-01-01';

question: How many orders were placed in the year 2022?
sql: SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_orders FROM orders WHERE EXTRACT(YEAR FROM order_created_at) = 2022;

question: What is the total revenue generated from orders that were shipped?
sql: SELECT SUM(o.order_total) AS total_revenue FROM orders o JOIN shipments s ON o.order_id = s.shipment_order_id WHERE s.shipment_status = 'shipped';

question: List the product names and their corresponding categories.
sql: SELECT p.product_name, c.category_name FROM products p JOIN category_products cp ON p.product_id = cp.category_product_product_id JOIN categories c ON cp.category_product_category_id = c.category_id;

question: Which users have not placed any orders?
sql: SELECT u.user_name FROM users u LEFT JOIN orders o ON u.user_id = o.order_user_id WHERE o.order_id IS NULL;

question: What are the names of vendors supplying products priced over $50?
sql: SELECT v.vendor_name FROM vendors v JOIN product_vendors pv ON v.vendor_id = pv.product_vendor_vendor_id JOIN products p ON pv.product_vendor_product_id = p.product_id WHERE p.product_price > 50;

question: How many products are in each category?

question: List the orders with their corresponding payment status.

question: What is the average rating for products in the 'Electronics' category?
sql: SELECT AVG(r.review_rating) AS average_rating FROM reviews r JOIN products p ON r.review_product_id = p.product_id JOIN category_products cp ON p.product_id = cp.category_product_product_id JOIN categories c ON cp.category_product_category_id = c.category_id WHERE c.category_name = 'Electronics';

question: Find the top 5 best-selling products.
sql: SELECT p.product_name, SUM(oi.order_item_quantity) AS total_sales FROM products p JOIN order_items oi ON p.product_id = oi.order_item_product_id GROUP BY p.product_name ORDER BY total_sales DESC LIMIT 5;

question: What are the total sales for each month in the year 2022?
sql: SELECT EXTRACT(MONTH FROM o.order_created_at) AS month, SUM(o.order_total) AS total_sales FROM orders o WHERE EXTRACT(YEAR FROM o.order_created_at) = 2022 GROUP BY month ORDER BY month;

question: Which products have an average review rating of 8 or higher, and what is their average rating?
sql:
SELECT p.product_id,
       p.product_name,
       AVG(r.review_rating) AS avg_rating
FROM products AS p
JOIN reviews AS r
    ON r.review_product_id = p.product_id
GROUP BY p.product_id, p.product_name
HAVING AVG(r.review_rating) >= 8
ORDER BY avg_rating DESC;

question: Which vendors supply more than 5 distinct products?
sql:
SELECT v.vendor_id,
       v.vendor_name,
       COUNT(DISTINCT pv.product_vendor_product_id) AS product_count
FROM vendors AS v
JOIN product_vendors AS pv
    ON pv.product_vendor_vendor_id = v.vendor_id
GROUP BY v.vendor_id, v.vendor_name
HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT pv.product_vendor_product_id) > 5;

question: What are the total quantities of each product purchased in delivered orders?
sql:
SELECT p.product_id,
       p.product_name,
       SUM(oi.order_item_quantity) AS total_quantity
FROM order_items AS oi
JOIN orders AS o
    ON oi.order_item_order_id = o.order_id
JOIN products AS p
    ON oi.order_item_product_id = p.product_id
WHERE o.order_status = 'delivered'
GROUP BY p.product_id, p.product_name
ORDER BY total_quantity DESC;

question: Which users have placed more than 3 orders that include at least one applied coupon?
sql:
SELECT u.user_id,
       u.user_name,
       COUNT(DISTINCT o.order_id) AS coupon_order_count
FROM users AS u
JOIN orders AS o
    ON o.order_user_id = u.user_id
JOIN order_coupons AS oc
    ON oc.order_coupon_order_id = o.order_id
GROUP BY u.user_id, u.user_name
HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT o.order_id) > 3;

question: List all active carts containing more than 2 items in total quantity.
sql:
SELECT c.cart_id,
       c.cart_user_id,
       SUM(ci.cart_item_quantity) AS total_items
FROM cart AS c
JOIN cart_items AS ci
    ON ci.cart_item_cart_id = c.cart_id
WHERE c.cart_status = 'active'
GROUP BY c.cart_id, c.cart_user_id
HAVING SUM(ci.cart_item_quantity) > 2;

question: What are the top 5 most-reviewed products created before 2024-01-01?
sql:
SELECT p.product_id,
       p.product_name,
       COUNT(r.review_id) AS review_count
FROM products AS p
JOIN reviews AS r
    ON r.review_product_id = p.product_id
WHERE p.product_created_at < '2024-01-01'
GROUP BY p.product_id, p.product_name
ORDER BY review_count DESC
LIMIT 5;

question: For each category, what is the average price of the products assigned to it?
sql:
SELECT c.category_id,
       c.category_name,
       AVG(p.product_price) AS avg_price
FROM categories AS c
JOIN category_products AS cp
    ON cp.category_product_category_id = c.category_id
JOIN products AS p
    ON p.product_id = cp.category_product_product_id
GROUP BY c.category_id, c.category_name
ORDER BY c.category_name;

question: Which shipments are currently in transit and going to addresses in California?
sql:
SELECT s.shipment_id,
       s.shipment_order_id,
       a.address_city,
       a.address_state
FROM shipments AS s
JOIN addresses AS a
    ON s.shipment_address_id = a.address_id
WHERE s.shipment_status = 'in_transit'
  AND a.address_state = 'California';

question: Which products have active discounts on 2025-01-01, and what are the discount percentages?
sql:
SELECT p.product_id,
       p.product_name,
       d.discount_percentage
FROM products AS p
JOIN product_discounts AS pd
    ON pd.product_discount_product_id = p.product_id
JOIN discounts AS d
    ON d.discount_id = pd.product_discount_discount_id
WHERE '2025-01-01' BETWEEN d.discount_start_date AND d.discount_end_date;

question: Which users submitted more than one return request in 2024?
sql:
SELECT u.user_id,
       u.user_name,
       COUNT(r.return_id) AS return_count
FROM users AS u
JOIN returns AS r
    ON r.return_user_id = u.user_id
WHERE r.return_created_at >= '2024-01-01'
  AND r.return_created_at < '2025-01-01'
GROUP BY u.user_id, u.user_name
HAVING COUNT(r.return_id) > 1;
